I'll solve this step by step to calculate the Quick Ratio and Net Profit Margin.

## Step 1: Calculate the Quick Ratio
The Quick Ratio formula is: (Current Assets - Inventory) / Current Liabilities

From the balance sheet:
- Current Assets = $10,453,882.43
- Inventory = $7,446,940.00
- Current Liabilities = $5,637,910.70

Quick Ratio = (Current Assets - Inventory) / Current Liabilities
Quick Ratio = ($10,453,882.43 - $7,446,940.00) / $5,637,910.70
Quick Ratio = $3,006,942.43 / $5,637,910.70
Quick Ratio = 0.5333

## Step 2: Calculate the Net Profit Margin
The Net Profit Margin formula is: (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%

From the income statement:
- Net Profit = $99,532.29
- Total Revenue = $836,813.79

Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%
Net Profit Margin = ($99,532.29 / $836,813.79) × 100%
Net Profit Margin = 0.1189 × 100%
Net Profit Margin = 11.89%
